snippet.textDisplay:
ARM has better IPC than x86, just due to legacy stuff with x86, so if it does manage to end up taking the performance crown for gaming, wouldn't be too surprised.
Still think RISC V is more likely to fully replace x86 in home, just due to licenses and then pretty much no baggage compared to even ARM. Issue there is more who's going to make them etc., Intel has bought the largest RISC V contributor though, so don't think Intel is too worried there.
